body:
@datalorax : Thanks for the patch.

This is added in https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1580 with the intention of allowing the admin to manually fix the data in internal topics like __consumer_offsets. It seems that in those cases, it's better to let the admin issue commitOffsetRequest instead of producing to the internal topics directly. 

So, I agree that it seems it's better to remove this logic. @jjkoshy : Since you suggested this change, what do you think?
